examples.en: Our relatives in Italy wined and dined us for a week.
They dined at the same slap-bang every day.
We were very well hosted and even dined at his house.
The bunch of grapes or stalk of garlic they frugally dined on.
They dined in an official capacity with other European leaders.
They dined on the restaurant speciality, Sicilian-style macaroni.
I have been racketing lately, having dined twice with Roger and once with Grant.
